1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,815
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i>

2
00:00:15,882 --> 00:00:20,220
has been continuously gaining

3
00:00:20,286 --> 00:00:21,955
-global popularity.
-That's true.

4
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:23,556
So we received a video message

5
00:00:23,623 --> 00:00:25,859
from a huge Hollywood star.

6
00:00:25,925 --> 00:00:26,960
A video message?

7
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:28,762
-Natalie Portman?
-Who is it?

8
00:00:28,828 --> 00:00:30,964
-Let's see it.
-Who is it?

9
00:00:41,608 --> 00:00:42,609
What?

10
00:00:42,675 --> 00:00:45,979
Are you serious?

11
00:00:50,417 --> 00:00:53,053
Wait, this is…

12
00:00:53,119 --> 00:00:55,321
It sounds like a challenge.

13
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:56,423
You're that big?

14
00:00:56,489 --> 00:00:57,457
-You?
-Is this real?

15
00:00:57,524 --> 00:00:58,792
It's from Jack Black.

16
00:00:58,858 --> 00:01:00,894
-It must be AI-generated.
-He knows who Poong is.

17
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:01,861
-And the show.
-Wait…

18
00:01:01,928 --> 00:01:05,198
Creative and bold dishes
are something I strive to make.

19
00:01:05,265 --> 00:01:07,333
-So why is Poong known for that?
-I wonder.

20
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,402
I guess something got lost
in the translation.

21
00:01:09,869 --> 00:01:11,838
MAYBE HIS NAME
WAS MISTRANSLATED?

22
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:14,340
-You should reply to his message.
-Should I?

23
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:15,675
Do it in English.

24
00:01:24,050 --> 00:01:24,984
ALREADY HITS A WALL

25
00:01:25,051 --> 00:01:25,985
Tell him it's not easy to cook.

26
00:01:31,257 --> 00:01:32,692
He used all the English he knows.

27
00:01:33,326 --> 00:01:36,062
You should come and join us
here at <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

28
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:39,833
I will… No, the chefs will make
something very delicious for you.

29
00:01:39,899 --> 00:01:40,834
Do join us sometime.

30
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,670
SHOW LOTS OF LOVE FOR
THE SUPER MARIO GALAXY MOVIE

31
00:01:43,736 --> 00:01:47,040
Allow me to introduce today's guests.

32
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:51,277
Two female warriors who made
K-culture a global phenomenon

33
00:01:51,344 --> 00:01:53,079
-are here with us today.
-Female warriors?

34
00:01:53,146 --> 00:01:54,747
Please welcome them with a big hand!

35
00:01:54,814 --> 00:01:56,483
Come on out!

36
00:01:57,717 --> 00:01:58,885
Today's fridge owners.

37
00:02:01,054 --> 00:02:03,156
The key figures
of the globally sensational film

38
00:02:03,223 --> 00:02:05,125
<i>KPop Demon Hunters!</i>

39
00:02:05,191 --> 00:02:07,861
Please welcome
Director Maggie Kang and Leejung!

40
00:02:07,927 --> 00:02:09,062
Welcome to the show!

41
00:02:09,662 --> 00:02:10,864
A GLOBAL K-CULTURE SENSATION

42
00:02:10,930 --> 00:02:13,266
<i>The hours viewed for this film</i>
<i>around the world</i>

43
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:14,567
<i>come to a total of 500 million.</i>

44
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:18,338
-Five hundred million, wow.
-The director of the biggest Netflix hit

45
00:02:18,404 --> 00:02:21,374
and the one who made
K-culture known around the world.

46
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:24,577
<i>The two-time winner of the Academy Awards,</i>

47
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:28,081
please welcome Director Maggie Kang
of <i>KPop Demon Hunters!</i>

48
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:31,951
Hello, I'm Maggie Kang,
the director of <i>KPop Demon Hunters.</i>

49
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:34,888
WELCOME TO THE SHOW

50
00:02:34,954 --> 00:02:36,389
Let me introduce the next guest.

51
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:39,025
<i>The most beloved K-pop choreographer</i>

52
00:02:39,092 --> 00:02:42,295
and the choreographer of "Soda Pop"
for <i>KPop Demon Hunters</i>,

53
00:02:42,362 --> 00:02:44,597
-please welcome dancer Leejung!
-Leejung!

54
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,166
-All right!
-Welcome.

55
00:02:46,232 --> 00:02:47,700
Welcome.

56
00:02:47,767 --> 00:02:50,003
KEY FIGURES BEHIND KPOP DEMON HUNTERS

57
00:02:50,069 --> 00:02:51,304
A stethoscope?

58
00:02:52,372 --> 00:02:53,640
Wait a minute.

59
00:02:53,706 --> 00:02:55,108
-One second.
-What?

60
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:57,243
He said Director Kang

61
00:02:57,310 --> 00:03:00,079
is wearing a stethoscope around her neck.

62
00:03:00,146 --> 00:03:01,948
-A stethoscope?
-I was so shocked!

63
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:03,917
YOU'RE ALREADY RUDE FROM THE GET-GO

64
00:03:03,983 --> 00:03:05,985
I'm so sorry!

65
00:03:06,052 --> 00:03:07,787
-Don't say that about a guest.
-Come on!

66
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:09,556
-It does look like one.
-A stethoscope?

67
00:03:09,622 --> 00:03:12,492
-A stethoscope? Come on.
-That was rude.

68
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:15,161
First, we have to begin with applause.

69
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:16,763
Congratulations on two Academy Awards.

70
00:03:16,829 --> 00:03:18,965
-Thank you.
-A two-time winner.

71
00:03:19,399 --> 00:03:21,367
SHE MADE NEW HISTORY FOR K-CULTURE

72
00:03:21,434 --> 00:03:22,902
-Thank you.
-This is huge.

73
00:03:22,969 --> 00:03:25,572
We're sitting here today
with a winner of an Academy Award.

74
00:03:25,638 --> 00:03:27,340
-It's a first.
-It is a first, isn't it?

75
00:03:27,407 --> 00:03:29,142
On top of that,

76
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:32,679
she brought the Oscar statuette

77
00:03:32,745 --> 00:03:34,280
-to the studio.
-Really?

78
00:03:34,347 --> 00:03:35,715
-Wow.
-I did.

79
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:37,016
Thank you for doing that.

80
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:39,419
-I brought it here.
-The real thing?

81
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:40,887
ALL EYES

82
00:03:40,954 --> 00:03:41,955
ON HER

83
00:03:42,021 --> 00:03:44,524
It fit perfectly in my bag.

84
00:03:44,591 --> 00:03:46,326
WHOAAA

85
00:03:47,126 --> 00:03:48,895
SEEING THE OSCAR STATUETTE IN PERSON

86
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:50,530
Wow.

87
00:03:50,597 --> 00:03:53,199
-I've never seen it before.
-Are we seeing the actual thing?

88
00:03:53,266 --> 00:03:55,735
It's the coolest-looking award
I've won to this day.

89
00:03:55,802 --> 00:03:56,636
Oh, really?

90
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:58,471
-And it's really heavy.
-Wait.

91
00:03:58,538 --> 00:04:00,607
You're carrying that in that bag?

92
00:04:00,673 --> 00:04:03,643
-Stashed into her tote bag.
-You don't have a case for it?

93
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,912
-There's no case?
-Other awards came in a case,

94
00:04:05,979 --> 00:04:07,981
but not this one.

95
00:04:08,715 --> 00:04:10,183
Because it's already heavy?

96
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,618
THE OSCAR STATUETTE COMES BARE

97
00:04:11,684 --> 00:04:14,020
-Hold it in your hand.
-Try and hold it, chefs.

98
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:16,656
-It's heavy.
-You won't get another chance to see it.

99
00:04:16,723 --> 00:04:17,924
MOM I WON AN AWARD

100
00:04:17,991 --> 00:04:20,159
I can't believe
I'm seeing it in real life.

101
00:04:20,226 --> 00:04:22,762
-May we take pictures with it?
-Yes, go ahead.

102
00:04:22,829 --> 00:04:24,897
That's for his social media!
He's obsessed!

103
00:04:24,964 --> 00:04:26,499
-He's obsessed.
-He'll upload that.

104
00:04:26,566 --> 00:04:28,401
What is it about him
and gaining followers?

105
00:04:28,468 --> 00:04:29,869
The social media addicts.

106
00:04:30,403 --> 00:04:31,604
TAKE ONE FOR ME TOO

107
00:04:32,538 --> 00:04:33,906
Sam is joining him too.

108
00:04:33,973 --> 00:04:36,309
-They'll upload it together.
-Sam has changed too.

109
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:39,846
THE PEEKERS

110
00:04:39,912 --> 00:04:42,315
-Wow. This is so cool.
-Isn't it?

111
00:04:42,382 --> 00:04:46,452
<i>-"Best Animated Feature Film of 2025."</i>
<i>-That's written on it?</i>

112
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:48,521
<i>Her name is on it too.</i>

113
00:04:48,588 --> 00:04:49,422
Put it right here,

114
00:04:49,489 --> 00:04:51,057
so it looks like we won Best TV Show.

115
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:52,425
Please put it there.

116
00:04:52,492 --> 00:04:54,794
-It looks so cool.
-<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> has won.

117
00:04:54,861 --> 00:04:56,329
TV SHOW OF THE YEAR

118
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:58,231
We have a winner
of the Academy Awards with us.

119
00:04:58,298 --> 00:04:59,465
MUST CAPTURE THIS MOMENT

120
00:04:59,532 --> 00:05:01,968
Once again, we'd like to thank everyone
at the Academy Awards.

121
00:05:02,035 --> 00:05:03,770
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> will continue to strive

122
00:05:03,836 --> 00:05:05,538
-to be the best show.
-We stole it.

123
00:05:05,605 --> 00:05:07,940
I'm sure we'll win it again next year.

124
00:05:08,274 --> 00:05:10,076
RESERVING THE NEXT YEAR'S AWARD TOO

125
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,712
-May we leave it here as we continue?
-Sure.

126
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:14,847
-It looks great.
-Right?

127
00:05:14,914 --> 00:05:16,783
Director Kang currently resides
in America,

128
00:05:16,849 --> 00:05:20,753
and she recently visited Korea
with a tight work schedule,

129
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:23,423
which included a visit
to <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

130
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:25,758
-Thank you so much for that.
-Sure.

131
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:28,094
-I'm a huge fan.
-Of our show?

132
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:30,630
I honestly felt less anxious at the Oscars

133
00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:34,067
than sitting here right now.

134
00:05:34,133 --> 00:05:37,036
-Really? You're more nervous now?
-Yes, I'm more nervous now.

135
00:05:37,103 --> 00:05:38,705
Oh, my.

136
00:05:38,771 --> 00:05:40,873
I'm very interested in cooking,

137
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:44,410
I cook often at home too,
and I know all the chefs here.

138
00:05:44,477 --> 00:05:46,045
And I watched both seasons of <i>CCW.</i>

139
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:47,280
THANK YOU

140
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:51,184
I also hear Leejung
is another huge fan of the show.

141
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:54,187
I seriously love this program

142
00:05:54,253 --> 00:05:55,722
so much.

143
00:05:55,788 --> 00:05:57,990
I always thought,
"I want to be a part of it someday,"

144
00:05:58,057 --> 00:06:00,827
but I literally have nothing in my fridge.

145
00:06:00,893 --> 00:06:04,664
So I figured it was a show
I could never be on.

146
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:06,532
But thanks to Director Kang,

147
00:06:06,599 --> 00:06:09,435
I got to be here as her plus one.
It's so wonderful.

148
00:06:09,502 --> 00:06:12,472
Leejung, was there a chef
you wanted to meet in person?

149
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:14,440
Yes, actually,

150
00:06:14,507 --> 00:06:16,776
I'm a huge fan of Chef Nam-no.

151
00:06:16,843 --> 00:06:18,277
-What? Really?
-Really?

152
00:06:18,344 --> 00:06:19,212
-What's happening?
-You're popular.

153
00:06:19,278 --> 00:06:20,113
You're a big shot.

154
00:06:20,179 --> 00:06:21,948
I have a favorite character

155
00:06:22,014 --> 00:06:23,816
from <i>KPop Demon Hunters,</i>

156
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:25,518
and he looks a lot like that character.

157
00:06:25,585 --> 00:06:27,453
-Really? Which one?
-Who?

158
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,821
He looks like Derpy.

159
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:30,923
<i>-Derpy!</i>
<i>-Really?</i>

160
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,225
TWO PEAS IN A POD

161
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:34,260
-Derpy is my favorite.
-The blue one.

162
00:06:34,327 --> 00:06:36,596
I thought she was going to say
the manager.

163
00:06:36,662 --> 00:06:38,097
-That manager.
-He looks like him.

164
00:06:38,164 --> 00:06:41,033
-The manager?
-He looks really cute.

165
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,869
-I can see the manager in him.
-He's Bobby!

166
00:06:42,935 --> 00:06:46,606
-He looks like the manager.
-It's half and half.

167
00:06:46,672 --> 00:06:48,007
All right.

168
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:49,242
Wait a minute.

169
00:06:49,308 --> 00:06:51,010
Her ideal type is someone else though.

170
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,979
-Her ideal type is someone else?
-Of course.

171
00:06:53,045 --> 00:06:54,580
-It's not Nam-no.
-That's life.

172
00:06:54,647 --> 00:06:56,449
-That's how it is.
-That's how life is.

173
00:06:56,516 --> 00:06:58,651
Have a drink. Drink up.

174
00:06:59,685 --> 00:07:01,487
Who's your ideal type?

175
00:07:01,554 --> 00:07:04,190
-Chef Hyun-suk, actually.
-Really?

176
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,826
-I thought it'd be Jong-won.
-This again?

177
00:07:06,893 --> 00:07:09,095
Come on. I can't deal with this.

178
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:11,564
In <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

179
00:07:11,631 --> 00:07:14,901
he led the mission aggressively
with conviction, right?

180
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:16,502
I saw that as leadership…

181
00:07:16,569 --> 00:07:18,004
-Is he asleep?
-…and learned from him.

182
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:20,573
Everyone, always have conviction
when you are cooking.

183
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,774
That's the way to cook…

184
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:23,009
I'm sorry.

185
00:07:23,075 --> 00:07:24,811
HE MUST'VE BEEN SO EXCITED…

186
00:07:24,877 --> 00:07:27,880
When we told Chef Hyun-suk
that Leejung would be here today,

187
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,449
he asked if it was Lee Jung, the singer.

188
00:07:29,515 --> 00:07:30,983
What are you talking about?

189
00:07:31,050 --> 00:07:33,486
-Stop making up stuff!
-Really?

190
00:07:33,553 --> 00:07:34,987
IT'S A COMPLETELY MADE-UP STORY

191
00:07:35,054 --> 00:07:36,656
Stop lying. Please.

192
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:37,790
I'll try harder.

193
00:07:37,857 --> 00:07:40,159
-I did not say that.
-He didn't.

194
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:42,061
HEHEHE…

195
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:45,131
What about Director Kang?
Anyone you wanted to meet?

196
00:07:45,198 --> 00:07:48,835
I wanted to meet Chef Hyun-suk too.

197
00:07:48,901 --> 00:07:50,703
-Oh, my.
-What?

198
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:53,806
-What's going on?
-I guess he's popular in the US.

199
00:07:53,873 --> 00:07:56,409
He's someone radiating with confidence.

200
00:07:57,944 --> 00:07:59,245
WATCH ME!

201
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:01,547
CONFIDENCE IS EVERYTHING!

202
00:08:01,614 --> 00:08:03,049
Back in the restroom, he said,

203
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:04,817
"The only animated film director I know

204
00:08:04,884 --> 00:08:08,488
-is Director Kim Cheong-gi."
-Leave him alone.

205
00:08:08,554 --> 00:08:11,123
-He only knows Director Kim Cheong-gi.
-Wait a minute.

206
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:13,693
-What's going on with you today?
-He's actually flustered.

207
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:15,127
Wait a minute.

208
00:08:15,194 --> 00:08:16,529
-Where are your knives?
-Director!

209
00:08:16,596 --> 00:08:18,531
May I have my knives?

210
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:20,833
-He's extra snappy today.
-Jeez.

211
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:23,069
-Good for you.
-He became so snappy

212
00:08:23,135 --> 00:08:25,171
after both guests said they liked him.

213
00:08:25,238 --> 00:08:26,439
IT DOESN'T HAPPEN OFTEN

214
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,441
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

215
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:31,410
Director Maggie Kang won
the Best Animated Feature Award

216
00:08:31,477 --> 00:08:34,714
in the Oscars with <i>KPop Demon Hunters,</i>

217
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:37,617
as well as the Best Original Song,
so two awards.

218
00:08:37,683 --> 00:08:40,987
-Everyone was touched by her speech.
-It was a big issue.

219
00:08:41,053 --> 00:08:43,723
It was so touching
to hear her mention Korea.

220
00:08:43,789 --> 00:08:44,790
What was it like there?

221
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:46,859
I was born in Korea,

222
00:08:46,926 --> 00:08:48,394
so whenever I visit,

223
00:08:48,461 --> 00:08:51,664
I feel like I have returned home.

224
00:08:51,731 --> 00:08:54,634
I'm someone who's full of Korean pride,

225
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:59,705
so I've always wanted to make a film
that showcases Korean culture.

226
00:08:59,772 --> 00:09:03,376
I also studied animation in college.

227
00:09:03,442 --> 00:09:05,711
She displayed all the beauty

228
00:09:05,778 --> 00:09:08,548
<i>and the essence of Korea in the film,</i>
<i>and it touched everyone's hearts.</i>

229
00:09:08,614 --> 00:09:10,416
I also choked up a little.

230
00:09:10,483 --> 00:09:12,118
THE CRAZE HIT THE ANIMATION MAJOR HARD

231
00:09:12,184 --> 00:09:13,853
He has stopped making webtoons.

232
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:15,488
No, I haven't.

233
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:17,823
-I'm going to do it. What do you mean?
-You will?

234
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,425
Director Kang must be an inspiration.

235
00:09:19,492 --> 00:09:22,028
-Yes, I want that statuette!
-Right?

236
00:09:22,094 --> 00:09:25,064
-I'm going to get back into it.
-Sure.

237
00:09:25,131 --> 00:09:26,732
In the touching moment

238
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:30,169
during the awards ceremony,
we saw a photo posted on the internet.

239
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:33,005
-It got a lot of people talking.
-What was it?

240
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:34,140
Let's see it.

241
00:09:34,206 --> 00:09:35,308
-I saw it too.
-What is it?

242
00:09:36,943 --> 00:09:38,210
It must be AI-generated.

243
00:09:38,277 --> 00:09:39,378
-It looks so good.
-Look.

244
00:09:39,445 --> 00:09:42,248
She called it "the perfect Oscars snack."

245
00:09:42,315 --> 00:09:45,051
-Uncooked <i>ramyeon?</i>
-Looks like she's eating uncooked <i>ramyeon</i>.

246
00:09:45,117 --> 00:09:46,819
It wasn't Photoshopped, was it?

247
00:09:46,886 --> 00:09:48,087
It wasn't.

248
00:09:48,154 --> 00:09:50,723
-We shared one.
-You did?

249
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,258
During the Oscars,

250
00:09:52,325 --> 00:09:54,327
you don't get a table or snacks,

251
00:09:54,393 --> 00:09:57,530
but the ceremony is quite long,
about four hours.

252
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,432
All you get is some popcorn,

253
00:09:59,498 --> 00:10:01,200
a bottle of water,

254
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:03,202
and some candies.

255
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:05,237
-That'll leave you hungry, right?
-Yes.

256
00:10:05,304 --> 00:10:07,006
I wanted to eat
some uncooked <i>ramyeon</i> there,

257
00:10:07,073 --> 00:10:09,475
so I even hid the chopsticks in my dress.

258
00:10:10,409 --> 00:10:11,811
-You did?
-Really?

259
00:10:12,244 --> 00:10:13,746
ON THE WAY TO THE CEREMONY

260
00:10:14,313 --> 00:10:16,215
CHOPSTICKS

261
00:10:16,716 --> 00:10:20,453
-So you brought it to eat it there?
-I did.

262
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:24,757
Thankfully, I was in a red dress,
so it went with my outfit too.

263
00:10:24,824 --> 00:10:25,858
It did.

264
00:10:25,925 --> 00:10:27,526
-It could look like a handbag.
-Yes.

265
00:10:27,593 --> 00:10:30,463
Yes, so I brought it in like a handbag.

266
00:10:30,529 --> 00:10:32,932
-That's such a power move.
-There's a chef here

267
00:10:32,999 --> 00:10:35,901
who actually felt the sensation
<i>KPop Demon Hunters</i> has become.

268
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:38,471
-It's Chef Jong-won.
-Right.

269
00:10:38,537 --> 00:10:41,440
I recently went to Hong Kong
for an awards ceremony for chefs,

270
00:10:41,507 --> 00:10:44,210
where many different Asian chefs
got together.

271
00:10:44,276 --> 00:10:47,313
I decided to wear <i>hanbok</i>,
our traditional Korean attire.

272
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:49,281
-Yes.
-Good call.

273
00:10:49,348 --> 00:10:53,653
I put on something called <i>changui</i>,
a type of an overcoat that scholars wore.

274
00:10:53,719 --> 00:10:55,454
And some people asked where my hat was.

275
00:10:55,521 --> 00:10:58,157
They said, "Where's your hat?"
I thought they were talking about

276
00:10:58,224 --> 00:11:00,493
a chef's hat since I'm a chef,
but I found out later

277
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:03,362
that they were asking about <i>gat</i>,
the hat they saw on <i>KPop Demon Hunters.</i>

278
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:06,999
GAT ALSO BECAME FAMOUS ALONG WITH THE FILM

279
00:11:07,066 --> 00:11:08,968
So they saw him as Saja Boys.

280
00:11:09,035 --> 00:11:10,603
He reminds me of Jinu.

281
00:11:10,936 --> 00:11:13,539
THE CENTER OF CHEF & MY FRIDGE BOYS,
SON JONG-WON

282
00:11:13,606 --> 00:11:17,410
Leejung participated as the choreographer.

283
00:11:17,476 --> 00:11:19,578
She choreographed the dance

284
00:11:19,645 --> 00:11:21,213
<i>to "How It's Done."</i>

285
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:24,083
THE OPENER
"HOW IT'S DONE" BY HUNTRIX

286
00:11:24,483 --> 00:11:27,119
LEEJUNG VERSION

287
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:28,554
<i>Also, the famous "Soda Pop."</i>

288
00:11:28,621 --> 00:11:30,990
"SODA POP" BY SAJA BOYS

289
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:34,860
<i>-A lot of people did the dance challenge.</i>
<i>-So many.</i>

290
00:11:34,927 --> 00:11:37,596
It's such a cool dance,

291
00:11:37,663 --> 00:11:39,498
especially the shoulder bop.

292
00:11:39,565 --> 00:11:42,468
That move was something
that drew attention

293
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:44,303
-of many people.
-Yes.

294
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:47,339
Do you watch it and think,
"I made something really good"?

295
00:11:47,406 --> 00:11:48,641
I can't help it.

296
00:11:50,176 --> 00:11:53,312
I've already choreographed
for many different artists,

297
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:55,715
but "Soda Pop" has to be

298
00:11:55,781 --> 00:11:57,516
the best work I have yet created.

299
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:59,318
BIG SMILE

300
00:11:59,685 --> 00:12:01,253
IT IS THE BEST

301
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,855
I'm so proud of that work.

302
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:05,291
The one who does this dance
even better than me, the creator,

303
00:12:05,357 --> 00:12:07,893
is Jinu, hands down. It's true.

304
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,663
-The Saja Boys are the best at it.
-I see.

305
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:14,233
All we ever get to watch
is Eun-yeong and Ho-young dance.

306
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,502
We always had to watch their messy dances,

307
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,304
and we finally got to watch a real dance.

308
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:20,806
I feel my eyes clearing up.

309
00:12:20,873 --> 00:12:21,907
I thought

310
00:12:21,974 --> 00:12:23,209
I wasn't so bad.

311
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:24,844
FAINTING(?)

312
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,278
How brazen is she?

313
00:12:26,345 --> 00:12:28,280
-You are good.
-I was pleased with myself.

314
00:12:28,347 --> 00:12:31,417
-"Pleased"?
-But after seeing Leejung today,

315
00:12:31,484 --> 00:12:33,285
I realized I was nothing but a lump.

316
00:12:33,352 --> 00:12:35,087
-Goodness, thank you.
-She's a choreographer.

317
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:36,722
FEELING BITTER(?)

318
00:12:36,789 --> 00:12:40,025
There were so many types of K-food
in the feature film, right?

319
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:41,894
Lots of Korean food was in it.

320
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:44,730
You get to see the characters
eat <i>seolleongtang, </i>ox bone soup.

321
00:12:44,797 --> 00:12:47,166
-And there was <i>gimbap.</i>
<i>-Gimbap.</i>

322
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:50,836
<i>They also ate </i>ramyeon
<i>just before their show.</i>

323
00:12:50,903 --> 00:12:52,338
Including the food scenes,

324
00:12:52,404 --> 00:12:56,142
what do you think was the part
that showcased the Korean culture best?

325
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:57,610
Which scene?

326
00:12:57,676 --> 00:13:00,846
When Huntrix eats
on the airplane in the beginning,

327
00:13:00,913 --> 00:13:03,983
they eat on the floor,
although there's a couch behind them.

328
00:13:04,049 --> 00:13:06,852
-That's true K-culture.
-That's true.

329
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:11,357
-Your couch is there as back support.
-Back support.

330
00:13:11,423 --> 00:13:14,827
They also use the green, spotty dishes.

331
00:13:14,894 --> 00:13:17,797
-Yes, for street foods like <i>tteokbokki</i>.
-Street foods.

332
00:13:17,863 --> 00:13:19,465
USED IN THE FILM

333
00:13:19,532 --> 00:13:22,234
-I put a lot of thought into it.
-We could tell.

334
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:25,404
After the huge success
of <i>KPop Demon Hunters,</i>

335
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:28,674
many people were interested
in the possibility of a sequel.

336
00:13:28,741 --> 00:13:31,844
Recently, the sequel has been confirmed!

337
00:13:31,911 --> 00:13:32,912
All right!

338
00:13:32,978 --> 00:13:34,680
EVERYONE APPLAUSES

339
00:13:34,747 --> 00:13:36,615
I'm already looking forward to it.

340
00:13:36,682 --> 00:13:37,783
Gosh.

341
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:41,153
I had a really tough time
making the first feature film.

342
00:13:42,288 --> 00:13:43,522
But the sequel

343
00:13:43,589 --> 00:13:45,224
has to be better than the first.

344
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:46,592
-Yes.
-That's true.

345
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:49,962
The action must be flashier,
and the plot must be more dramatic.

346
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:52,298
So I'm a little nervous,

347
00:13:52,364 --> 00:13:53,833
but I'll do my best.

348
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:55,301
May I share something that I know?

349
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:57,203
-What is it?
-There's a musical genre

350
00:13:57,269 --> 00:13:59,405
she wants to use in <i>KPop Demon Hunters 2.</i>

351
00:13:59,471 --> 00:14:02,141
She brought up trot.

352
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:03,776
-Trot?
-Yes.

353
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:05,711
-That's Korean too.
-That's true.

354
00:14:05,778 --> 00:14:07,046
My mom

355
00:14:07,112 --> 00:14:09,582
is a huge fan of Lim Young-woong.

356
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:10,749
A REQUEST FROM A FAN

357
00:14:10,816 --> 00:14:14,553
-She was influential.
-She asked if I could include trot music,

358
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:18,324
but I'm not sure yet.
If it goes well with the story, then yes.

359
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,458
It's easy to see

360
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,861
she has a lot of affection for Korea
by the way she speaks.

361
00:14:21,927 --> 00:14:25,731
It's now time to go through
Director Maggie Kang's fridge.

362
00:14:25,798 --> 00:14:29,301
She currently resides in America,

363
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:33,305
so we couldn't acquire her actual fridge.

364
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:35,507
So today,

365
00:14:35,574 --> 00:14:40,512
we've filled it up
with Korean food ingredients she loves.

366
00:14:40,579 --> 00:14:42,681
Let's take a look inside.

367
00:14:42,748 --> 00:14:46,652
What does Director Maggie Kang
keep in her fridge?

368
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:48,520
-We present her fridge!
-Fridge!

369
00:14:51,023 --> 00:14:52,858
LOTS OF K-FOOD INGREDIENTS

370
00:14:52,925 --> 00:14:55,361
First of all, every shelf
has a different theme.

371
00:14:55,427 --> 00:14:59,832
The top shelf has ingredients that are
better in Korea than anywhere abroad.

372
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,033
The second shelf

373
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:05,170
has K-food ingredients
full of Director Kang's memories.

374
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:09,642
The third shelf has
the stuff she enjoys even in America.

375
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:12,011
-Let's go through each theme.
-Let's do that.

376
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:13,145
This one.

377
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:14,980
-Watermelon.
-Watermelon.

378
00:15:15,047 --> 00:15:16,048
Tangerine.

379
00:15:16,115 --> 00:15:17,583
I see strawberries back there.

380
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:18,884
Also, Korean melon.

381
00:15:18,951 --> 00:15:22,021
Are these all better in Korea
than in America?

382
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:25,391
-Yes, strawberries are so different.
-That's so true.

383
00:15:25,457 --> 00:15:26,725
Yes, strawberries are different.

384
00:15:26,792 --> 00:15:29,261
Korean strawberries are the best.
The ones from Nonsan.

385
00:15:29,328 --> 00:15:31,063
I was disappointed
with strawberries in America.

386
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:34,033
So I always eat lots of strawberries
whenever I come here.

387
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:37,670
These must be carrots.

388
00:15:37,736 --> 00:15:39,238
-Perilla leaves.
-Chives.

389
00:15:39,305 --> 00:15:41,507
Also, zucchini and shiitake.

390
00:15:41,573 --> 00:15:43,142
Are carrots different too?

391
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:45,611
Carrots are pretty thin over there,

392
00:15:45,678 --> 00:15:48,480
and they taste more earthy.

393
00:15:48,547 --> 00:15:53,085
Korean carrots are sweeter
and much juicier.

394
00:15:53,152 --> 00:15:54,753
Perilla leaves

395
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:56,989
are so expensive there. They're pricey.

396
00:15:57,056 --> 00:15:59,725
Ten perilla leaves
wrapped with a rubber band

397
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,760
cost three dollars.

398
00:16:01,827 --> 00:16:03,762
-Are you serious?
-That's so expensive.

399
00:16:03,829 --> 00:16:05,664
-That's 4,500 won.
-I should start a business.

400
00:16:05,731 --> 00:16:07,433
-It's so expensive.
-It's about 5,000 won.

401
00:16:07,499 --> 00:16:10,302
-So I can't have them often.
-It's expensive.

402
00:16:10,369 --> 00:16:12,137
I'd end up spending 300,000 won
just on those.

403
00:16:12,204 --> 00:16:13,305
I eat so many perilla leaves.

404
00:16:13,572 --> 00:16:15,841
NO ONE EATS 600 LEAVES PER MEAL…

405
00:16:15,908 --> 00:16:17,509
-What about milk?
-Milk.

406
00:16:17,576 --> 00:16:20,212
Korean milk tastes much richer.

407
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:21,613
She's right.

408
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:24,783
That's why Korean ice cream
tastes much better.

409
00:16:26,018 --> 00:16:30,589
I'm someone
who isn't into sweets and desserts,

410
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:34,426
but I have to eat ice cream
every single day in Korea.

411
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:37,496
Otherwise, I go back
and regret not having more.

412
00:16:37,563 --> 00:16:39,465
Ice cream. There it is.

413
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:41,333
Is this something you like?

414
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:43,002
-That's delicious.
-Yes, it's good.

415
00:16:43,068 --> 00:16:44,436
It's vanilla ice cream.

416
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,405
Do you know the name of the original one?

417
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:47,606
THE ORIGINAL ONE?

418
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,041
Back in the day, there was Foremost.

419
00:16:49,108 --> 00:16:50,042
-What?
-What now?

420
00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:52,277
-What?
-It was called Foremost Ice Cream.

421
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:53,645
-What year was that?
-Foremost?

422
00:16:53,712 --> 00:16:54,747
-I knew it.
-I see.

423
00:16:54,813 --> 00:16:56,749
This is why we need a grandpa.

424
00:16:56,815 --> 00:16:58,550
That way, we can learn our history.

425
00:16:58,617 --> 00:17:00,052
Tell us about the old days, Grandpa.

426
00:17:00,119 --> 00:17:02,054
It's nice to be here
with a history teacher.

427
00:17:02,321 --> 00:17:04,690
THE LIVING MUSEUM

428
00:17:04,757 --> 00:17:07,559
The second shelf
has ingredients of her memories.

429
00:17:07,626 --> 00:17:11,196
-Hyun-suk can chime in once again.
-All right.

430
00:17:11,263 --> 00:17:13,665
The second shelf. There's <i>chwinamul</i>.

431
00:17:13,732 --> 00:17:14,900
And <i>chamnamul</i>.

432
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,535
Bracken. <i>Gobi</i>.

433
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:18,937
-You must love <i>namul</i>, seasoned greens.
-I do.

434
00:17:19,004 --> 00:17:22,441
My mother makes
really delicious <i>namul</i> dishes,

435
00:17:22,508 --> 00:17:25,911
so she made them often,
and I grew up eating lots of those.

436
00:17:25,978 --> 00:17:29,381
While growing up in Canada,
when we wanted these greens,

437
00:17:29,448 --> 00:17:32,284
we'd go to a golf course or a park

438
00:17:32,351 --> 00:17:33,185
and pick them.

439
00:17:33,485 --> 00:17:35,354
SNEAKING BRACKEN

440
00:17:35,421 --> 00:17:37,623
I went around to pick them annually.

441
00:17:37,923 --> 00:17:38,924
NOT ALLOWED ANYMORE

442
00:17:38,991 --> 00:17:40,959
-People there don't eat those.
-They don't.

443
00:17:41,026 --> 00:17:44,663
Back when many Koreans emigrated abroad…

444
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,198
-Here it comes.
-…this happened often.

445
00:17:46,265 --> 00:17:47,733
-They'd often pick mugwort.
-Mugwort.

446
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,135
-And it was all to eat them.
-Yes.

447
00:17:50,202 --> 00:17:51,870
Once upon a time.

448
00:17:51,937 --> 00:17:54,606
-I see some <i>naengmyeon</i> ingredients too.
-Yes.

449
00:17:54,673 --> 00:17:56,308
-Pyongyang style?
-Pyongyang <i>naengmyeon</i>.

450
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:57,209
Pyongyang <i>naengmyeon</i>.

451
00:17:57,276 --> 00:18:01,146
My grandmother on my father's side
made good Pyongyang <i>naengmyeon</i>.

452
00:18:01,213 --> 00:18:03,449
-She made it herself? At home?
-Yes, she made it.

453
00:18:03,515 --> 00:18:07,019
So I remember growing up
eating that quite often.

454
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,555
What other noodle dishes do you enjoy<i>?</i>

455
00:18:09,621 --> 00:18:12,224
I love them all. I love all noodle dishes.

456
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,059
She even ate uncooked <i>ramyeon</i>.

457
00:18:14,126 --> 00:18:16,161
-Of course, she likes them.
-Yes, that's true.

458
00:18:16,228 --> 00:18:19,298
I usually prefer thinner noodles.

459
00:18:19,965 --> 00:18:22,935
-Such as banquet noodles?
-Yes.

460
00:18:23,001 --> 00:18:24,570
According to a tip,

461
00:18:24,636 --> 00:18:26,905
Director Kang is actually

462
00:18:26,972 --> 00:18:28,674
an excellent cook.

463
00:18:28,740 --> 00:18:31,643
I wouldn't say I'm an excellent cook.

464
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:34,079
I enjoy doing it. I enjoy the process.

465
00:18:34,146 --> 00:18:37,883
-What do you think is your best dish?
-I like to make <i>yukgaejang.</i>

466
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,618
-You make <i>yukgaejang?</i>
-I do.

467
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:41,220
I make kimchi at home too.

468
00:18:41,487 --> 00:18:42,621
WOW

469
00:18:42,688 --> 00:18:44,356
-She makes kimchi?
-You make it yourself?

470
00:18:44,423 --> 00:18:45,991
I make napa cabbage kimchi

471
00:18:46,058 --> 00:18:47,226
and diced radish kimchi.

472
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:50,329
Korean markets probably sell some,
but you choose to make them?

473
00:18:50,395 --> 00:18:52,731
Yes, it's more delicious

474
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:54,133
and can be kept longer.

475
00:18:54,199 --> 00:18:55,834
-That's true.
-You must be a good cook

476
00:18:55,901 --> 00:18:57,336
if you make kimchi at home.

477
00:18:57,402 --> 00:18:58,971
I like to cook.

478
00:18:59,037 --> 00:19:03,442
Now, the third shelf.
Ingredients she enjoys even in America.

479
00:19:03,509 --> 00:19:05,277
Rice cake for <i>tteokguk,</i> rice cake soup?

480
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:07,412
Do you enjoy <i>tteokguk</i> often?

481
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:10,149
I don't particularly like <i>tteok</i>,

482
00:19:10,215 --> 00:19:13,852
but my daughter, Rumi, loves it so much.

483
00:19:13,919 --> 00:19:16,255
She even takes some
as her lunch to school.

484
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:18,023
-<i>Tteokguk?</i>
-Yes, she takes <i>tteokguk.</i>

485
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:20,626
It can get soggy after a while.

486
00:19:20,692 --> 00:19:22,394
She must like it that way too.

487
00:19:22,461 --> 00:19:23,962
It's even more delicious.

488
00:19:24,029 --> 00:19:26,532
One day, she asked me to pack kimchi.

489
00:19:26,598 --> 00:19:29,067
So I said, "But it could smell."

490
00:19:29,134 --> 00:19:32,504
"You probably shouldn't take it."

491
00:19:32,571 --> 00:19:34,339
Then she replied,

492
00:19:34,406 --> 00:19:37,042
"It's what I like,
so I want to take it to school."

493
00:19:37,109 --> 00:19:38,443
-I see.
-When I was younger,

494
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:41,380
-I could never take kimchi to school.
-Right.

495
00:19:41,446 --> 00:19:42,648
I was embarrassed and it smells,

496
00:19:42,714 --> 00:19:45,551
-and others hated it.
-Other kids would say something.

497
00:19:45,617 --> 00:19:48,220
But she said, "I don't care."

498
00:19:48,287 --> 00:19:49,454
And she finished it at school.

499
00:19:50,622 --> 00:19:51,456
How adorable.

500
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:53,559
When you mentioned your daughter,
was she named…

501
00:19:53,625 --> 00:19:55,360
-Rumi.
-Rumi?

502
00:19:55,427 --> 00:19:56,495
Isn't that the name

503
00:19:56,562 --> 00:19:59,198
-of Huntrix's leader?
-That's right.

504
00:19:59,264 --> 00:20:01,833
I made the character first

505
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:03,502
and wrote down the name Rumi.

506
00:20:03,569 --> 00:20:06,171
I was pregnant when I was
in process of making the character.

507
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:08,473
When I found out that I was having a girl,

508
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:11,410
I loved the name Rumi,
so I named her that.

509
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:13,078
AMAZED

510
00:20:13,145 --> 00:20:16,148
There are scenes
with young Rumi in the film,

511
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:20,686
and my daughter was the one
who did the voice acting and singing.

512
00:20:20,752 --> 00:20:21,620
She's in the film.

513
00:20:21,687 --> 00:20:23,155
Is that so?

514
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,591
-Your daughter's voice?
-Yes.

515
00:20:25,657 --> 00:20:27,259
Feel free to use my name at no charge.

516
00:20:28,193 --> 00:20:29,428
Hwani?

517
00:20:29,494 --> 00:20:31,697
-Or Ruhwani. Call me anything you like.
-Hwani.

518
00:20:31,763 --> 00:20:32,864
HE WANTS AT LEAST HIS NAME IN IT

519
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:35,200
She might use one of our names.

520
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:37,135
-I'll remember that.
-Okay.

521
00:20:37,202 --> 00:20:39,571
I found this <i>sikhye</i>, sweet rice punch.

522
00:20:39,638 --> 00:20:41,607
I've always wanted to try making it.

523
00:20:41,673 --> 00:20:43,242
-Wow.
-With malt?

524
00:20:43,308 --> 00:20:44,276
Can you make it?

525
00:20:44,343 --> 00:20:46,712
You can make it with some malt.

526
00:20:46,778 --> 00:20:48,614
I doubt it's easy.

527
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:51,216
-Use a rice cooker. It's easy.
-People often use a rice cooker.

528
00:20:51,283 --> 00:20:52,551
Is it easy? I see.

529
00:20:52,618 --> 00:20:54,786
Let's move on to the freezer.

530
00:20:54,853 --> 00:20:56,421
Pork, chicken,

531
00:20:56,488 --> 00:20:58,023
-and beef.
-And beef.

532
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,124
What's here?

533
00:20:59,658 --> 00:21:01,827
-Blue crabs!
-Blue crabs.

534
00:21:01,893 --> 00:21:04,796
Aren't American lobsters
better than blue crabs?

535
00:21:04,863 --> 00:21:07,933
I like the flavor of crab
more than lobster.

536
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,768
-I see.
-Blue crabs are good.

537
00:21:09,835 --> 00:21:11,637
-Crab meat is delicious.
-Blue crab is good.

538
00:21:11,703 --> 00:21:12,904
Shelf-stable ingredients.

539
00:21:12,971 --> 00:21:14,606
Why do you have so much seaweed for soup?

540
00:21:14,673 --> 00:21:16,942
Look at all this <i>miyeok</i>.

541
00:21:17,009 --> 00:21:18,944
-Do you like these?
-I really do,

542
00:21:19,011 --> 00:21:20,545
and I have a lot at home.

543
00:21:20,612 --> 00:21:21,913
-I see.
-But the thing is,

544
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:23,649
all I ever make with it is soup.

545
00:21:23,715 --> 00:21:26,818
So I want to learn other recipes
that use dried seaweed.

546
00:21:26,885 --> 00:21:29,655
WANTS DIFFERENT RECIPES TO USE SEAWEED

547
00:21:29,721 --> 00:21:31,957
Leejung, do you also have
a deep connection with seaweed?

548
00:21:32,024 --> 00:21:34,660
The only dish I know how to make
is seaweed soup, <i>miyeok-guk.</i>

549
00:21:34,726 --> 00:21:36,228
-<i>Miyeok-guk.</i>
-The only one?

550
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:39,498
-That's about it.
-You just know how to make <i>miyeok-guk?</i>

551
00:21:39,564 --> 00:21:41,633
I guess all beauties like seaweed.

552
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,236
BEAUTIES LOVE SEAWEED

553
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:45,570
I like seaweed too.

554
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:47,472
-You're an exception.
-I like seaweed too.

555
00:21:47,539 --> 00:21:50,909
That was all
for Director Maggie Kang's fridge!

556
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:52,711
FINISHED CHECKING OUT HER FRIDGE

557
00:21:52,778 --> 00:21:57,049
Now, let's find out
what she wants to order.

558
00:21:57,115 --> 00:22:00,218
These are her orders. Show us!

559
00:22:00,285 --> 00:22:01,753
I wonder what they are.

560
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:04,156
Both orders are revealed at once.

561
00:22:04,222 --> 00:22:05,757
K-Pop <i>Miyeok </i>Hunters.

562
00:22:05,824 --> 00:22:07,025
HEHEHE

563
00:22:07,092 --> 00:22:07,926
-K-Food.
-K-Food.

564
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:11,930
-It's K-Food. K-Food <i>Miyeok </i>Hunters.
-K-Food <i>Miyeok </i>Hunters.

565
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:13,131
KMH.

566
00:22:13,198 --> 00:22:15,834
The roasted seaweed, <i>gim</i>,
is widely known these days,

567
00:22:15,901 --> 00:22:17,169
but not <i>miyeok,</i> the ones for soup.

568
00:22:17,235 --> 00:22:21,873
So I want to see a dish
that can showcase <i>miyeok</i> in some way.

569
00:22:21,940 --> 00:22:24,643
You wish to introduce <i>miyeok</i>
to the world, right?

570
00:22:24,710 --> 00:22:26,645
-That's what she wants.
-I see.

571
00:22:26,712 --> 00:22:29,948
The next order is named
K-Food Inspo for <i>KDH 2.</i>

572
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:32,017
<i>Just as how they chugged </i>seolleongtang,

573
00:22:32,084 --> 00:22:36,521
I want to present a new K-Food
through the film.

574
00:22:36,588 --> 00:22:38,523
-She has a lot on her mind.
-Of course.

575
00:22:38,590 --> 00:22:40,759
She has to do a good job with the sequel.

576
00:22:40,826 --> 00:22:42,327
-I need your help.
-Yes.

577
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:44,229
You have to give her something, chefs.

578
00:22:44,296 --> 00:22:45,931
Give her inspiration.

579
00:22:45,997 --> 00:22:48,934
-She wants to be inspired by you.
-That's right.

580
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,736
Your name might make it into the credits.

581
00:22:50,802 --> 00:22:53,004
Right. "Special thanks to…"

582
00:22:53,405 --> 00:22:55,073
NOT A BAD IDEA

583
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:57,642
"Featuring so-and-so." It might happen.

584
00:22:58,176 --> 00:22:59,344
LICKING LIPS

585
00:22:59,411 --> 00:23:01,580
As you can see in front of the orders,

586
00:23:01,646 --> 00:23:02,781
we have special rounds today,

587
00:23:02,848 --> 00:23:06,918
-a team round and a tag-team round.
-A tag-team round?

588
00:23:06,985 --> 00:23:10,288
For the team round, you'll team up in twos

589
00:23:10,355 --> 00:23:13,024
-and fight two-on-two.
-As teams.

590
00:23:13,091 --> 00:23:14,259
As for the tag-team round,

591
00:23:14,326 --> 00:23:19,297
the teammates must take turns
and cook within the same 15 minutes.

592
00:23:19,364 --> 00:23:21,600
-Only one at a time?
-One at a time.

593
00:23:21,666 --> 00:23:23,101
It's a relay round.

594
00:23:23,168 --> 00:23:26,538
Teamwork may be important
depending on what you'll make.

595
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:27,873
We may see a stroke of genius.

596
00:23:27,939 --> 00:23:30,909
And now, we'll wait for you to volunteer.

597
00:23:31,476 --> 00:23:32,844
Shouldn't the old man give the inspo?

598
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:36,748
-He's a guy full of inspiration.
-Old man.

599
00:23:36,815 --> 00:23:38,617
-Old man.
-The old man's inspo?

600
00:23:38,683 --> 00:23:42,821
-Chef Hyun-suk is a big inspiration.
-Will <i>KDH 2</i> depict an old man?

601
00:23:42,888 --> 00:23:45,090
-Wearing <i>gat, dopo</i>, and the works.
-This old man

602
00:23:45,157 --> 00:23:47,159
will not choose to provide inspo,

603
00:23:47,225 --> 00:23:49,661
but go for K-Food <i>Miyeok </i>Hunters.

604
00:23:50,028 --> 00:23:51,663
GLAD TO HAVE YOU

605
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:54,800
-He used seaweed and became known.
-Yes, the halibut <i>miyeok-guk</i>.

606
00:23:54,866 --> 00:24:00,272
I'll also make something creative
that will inspire her in that round.

607
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:02,974
You'll need a partner.

608
00:24:03,041 --> 00:24:05,143
-Your partner…
-Your partner…

609
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:07,813
-That's nice.
-I'll join him as a teammate.

610
00:24:07,879 --> 00:24:10,315
-Wait.
-Wait, ask him first.

611
00:24:10,382 --> 00:24:11,883
I'll join him.

612
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:13,652
BONE-CHILLING

613
00:24:14,219 --> 00:24:16,988
It's not a bad idea to try and work
as Team Choi and Poong.

614
00:24:17,055 --> 00:24:18,457
Wait a second.

615
00:24:18,523 --> 00:24:19,591
I think I can win against them.

616
00:24:19,658 --> 00:24:22,561
-It's not so bad for me.
-It's not?

617
00:24:22,627 --> 00:24:23,995
While we're working together,

618
00:24:24,062 --> 00:24:26,364
he'll be within reach.

619
00:24:26,431 --> 00:24:27,599
You can get mad at him.

620
00:24:27,666 --> 00:24:30,035
-It's better to keep him within reach.
-Of course.

621
00:24:30,101 --> 00:24:32,037
You can give him a lesson too.

622
00:24:32,103 --> 00:24:34,473
All right, then. Let's see.

623
00:24:34,539 --> 00:24:35,373
The team round.

624
00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:37,876
US?

625
00:24:38,176 --> 00:24:39,311
I'M ALL FOR IT

626
00:24:39,377 --> 00:24:41,112
NOT ANOTHER CHEF, BUT YOU

627
00:24:41,179 --> 00:24:42,914
Only one of them will suffer.

628
00:24:42,981 --> 00:24:44,382
Stay out if you don't like it.

629
00:24:44,449 --> 00:24:45,650
-I think it'll be okay.
-Really?

630
00:24:45,717 --> 00:24:46,885
We've done it once before.

631
00:24:46,952 --> 00:24:48,487
-You've been a team.
-We have.

632
00:24:48,553 --> 00:24:51,756
-Ho-young and Sam join the team round.
-KMH.

633
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:54,960
Next, K-Food Inspo for <i>KDH 2.</i>

634
00:24:55,026 --> 00:24:56,828
Is that another two-on-two round?

635
00:24:56,895 --> 00:24:58,997
-Yes.
-No, let's not do two-on-two.

636
00:24:59,064 --> 00:25:01,132
-How about three-on-one?
-Three-on-one?

637
00:25:01,199 --> 00:25:02,133
WHAT?

638
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,235
-Three-on-one.
-Three-on-one?

639
00:25:03,301 --> 00:25:06,404
-Three doesn't sound so bad.
-Three against one sounds fun.

640
00:25:06,471 --> 00:25:08,974
-If it's possible.
-We've never done that.

641
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:12,143
Jong-won has the most stars
among the four.

642
00:25:12,210 --> 00:25:14,045
-Five stars.
-Is that okay?

643
00:25:14,112 --> 00:25:15,547
From the looks of it,

644
00:25:15,614 --> 00:25:17,315
-it'll probably be us.
-Yes.

645
00:25:17,382 --> 00:25:18,817
<i>But when we come together,</i>

646
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:21,219
-we become worse.
-It doesn't work well.

647
00:25:21,286 --> 00:25:22,888
So we'll need Chef Eun-yeong,

648
00:25:22,954 --> 00:25:24,956
which means
the young guns will come together.

649
00:25:25,357 --> 00:25:26,858
WILL THE 3 YOUNG GUNS TEAM UP?

650
00:25:26,925 --> 00:25:28,994
Is that okay with you? Can we do that?

651
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:30,295
Let's do this.

652
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:32,130
-I'll try.
-Will you give it a go?

653
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:36,301
The tag-team round

654
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:39,804
is Jong-won versus Nam-no,
Eun-yeong, and Sung-jun.

655
00:25:39,871 --> 00:25:41,806
K-Food <i>Miyeok </i>Hunters.

656
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:44,376
Let us begin the team round,

657
00:25:44,442 --> 00:25:46,611
Hyun-suk and Poong
versus Ho-young and Sam!

658
00:25:46,678 --> 00:25:47,779
You got this!

659
00:25:49,814 --> 00:25:54,085
<i>The first round, played with ingredients</i>
<i>from a two-time Oscar winner,</i>

660
00:25:54,152 --> 00:25:56,087
Director Maggie Kang, is about to begin.

661
00:25:56,154 --> 00:25:58,356
"All I need is Sam."

662
00:25:58,423 --> 00:26:00,158
Chef Ho-young and Chef Sam are up.

663
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:02,527
"I just need to get rid of Poong."

664
00:26:02,594 --> 00:26:05,430
Chef Hyun-suk and Webtoon Artist Poong
are also up.

665
00:26:05,497 --> 00:26:08,233
Ho-young and Sam
have cooked together as a team

666
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,968
<i>in </i>Culinary Class Wars 2.

667
00:26:10,035 --> 00:26:11,636
-Yes.
-But it's the first time

668
00:26:11,703 --> 00:26:13,705
for Hyun-suk and Poong to team up
in our history.

669
00:26:13,772 --> 00:26:16,107
Chef Hyun-suk has always been

670
00:26:16,174 --> 00:26:18,143
-nothing but harsh on me.
-Right.

671
00:26:18,209 --> 00:26:21,680
But I've come very far
and am now on par with him.

672
00:26:21,746 --> 00:26:23,081
ON PAR? REALLY?

673
00:26:23,148 --> 00:26:25,283
-I'm impressed with myself.
-I'm sure.

674
00:26:25,350 --> 00:26:27,152
If you think about it,

675
00:26:27,218 --> 00:26:30,322
we've worked as a team,
so we'll probably have better teamwork.

676
00:26:30,388 --> 00:26:32,857
Then do you have a leader?

677
00:26:32,924 --> 00:26:35,293
It's Ho-young? He's the leader.

678
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:38,897
-And this side…
-He's the head, and Poong's the sous chef.

679
00:26:38,964 --> 00:26:41,866
The four of them
have been with the show for a long time,

680
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:43,134
so they know each other so well.

681
00:26:43,201 --> 00:26:44,669
-They do.
-That's true.

682
00:26:44,736 --> 00:26:46,805
-That's why Sam said this.
-Huh?

683
00:26:46,871 --> 00:26:48,673
-Do we have a transcript?
-We do.

684
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:50,408
We've been tapping their green room.

685
00:26:50,475 --> 00:26:52,110
"I already know what will happen."

686
00:26:52,177 --> 00:26:53,945
"Hyun-suk will take the <i>miyeok</i>

687
00:26:54,512 --> 00:26:55,880
and grind it."

688
00:26:57,082 --> 00:26:58,850
-The main ingredient is <i>miyeok</i>.
-Again?

689
00:26:58,917 --> 00:27:01,086
-So you're sure of it?
-I'm 100% sure.

690
00:27:01,152 --> 00:27:02,354
He'll grind it.

691
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:03,955
Also, Poong will get

692
00:27:04,022 --> 00:27:05,190
severely reprimanded.

693
00:27:07,058 --> 00:27:08,593
You can see it happening?

694
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,228
-That's what I think.
-I see.

695
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:11,896
He says I always grind stuff,

696
00:27:11,963 --> 00:27:14,332
but who cares? We always have new guests.

697
00:27:14,399 --> 00:27:16,835
-If the guests are new, it doesn't matter!
-That's true.

698
00:27:16,901 --> 00:27:18,036
They're always different.

699
00:27:18,103 --> 00:27:19,137
CONVINCED

700
00:27:19,204 --> 00:27:21,306
They're quite alike.

701
00:27:21,373 --> 00:27:24,242
-It's a new dish for them.
-So the prediction must be right.

702
00:27:24,309 --> 00:27:25,410
I don't want the viewers

703
00:27:25,477 --> 00:27:27,112
to think that this is a rerun.

704
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:31,950
The guests may change,
but our viewers are always tuning in.

705
00:27:32,017 --> 00:27:33,885
They're pretty feisty today.

706
00:27:33,952 --> 00:27:36,588
Poong, any predictions
for what that team will do?

707
00:27:36,888 --> 00:27:37,922
PEEKS

708
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:39,424
They'll obviously

709
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:41,192
make fresh udon noodles.

710
00:27:42,260 --> 00:27:44,729
And it'll be topped
with something deep-fried.

711
00:27:45,630 --> 00:27:46,865
TRIES TO REMAIN CALM
HA, HA, HA, HA

712
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:49,567
-I can see it already.
-Because Ho-young is the leader?

713
00:27:50,368 --> 00:27:52,237
TEAM HO-YOUNG & SAM'S INGREDIENTS:
MIYEOK, PORK BELLY, SHRIMP

714
00:27:52,303 --> 00:27:54,572
CHICKEN STOCK, KELP, BONITO FLAKES,
CUCUMBER, BREADCRUMB, ABALONE, AND MORE

715
00:27:54,639 --> 00:27:58,076
Ho-young and Sam, what are you two making?

716
00:27:58,143 --> 00:28:01,379
We're going to make
three different seaweed dishes.

717
00:28:01,446 --> 00:28:02,747
First…

718
00:28:02,814 --> 00:28:04,349
HESITATES

719
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:05,950
I'll make thin noodles…

720
00:28:06,217 --> 00:28:07,152
NOODLES?

721
00:28:07,719 --> 00:28:10,055
-…and make udon.
-You are making udon!

722
00:28:10,121 --> 00:28:12,257
-It was udon!
-See?

723
00:28:12,323 --> 00:28:13,792
I'll make udon

724
00:28:13,858 --> 00:28:16,594
-and make it cold.
-Cold udon.

725
00:28:16,661 --> 00:28:20,165
I'll serve it with seaweed sauce
for her to eat it with.

726
00:28:20,231 --> 00:28:21,399
The second dish

727
00:28:21,466 --> 00:28:24,102
is sweet and sour seaweed salad
with abalone and shrimps.

728
00:28:24,169 --> 00:28:25,470
-That sounds good.
-Lastly…

729
00:28:25,537 --> 00:28:26,471
That sounds good.

730
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:27,972
…I saw some shrimp meat.

731
00:28:28,039 --> 00:28:30,175
I'll mix them with pork belly,
wrap them with seaweed,

732
00:28:30,241 --> 00:28:31,776
and make seaweed <i>menbosha</i>.

733
00:28:31,843 --> 00:28:33,878
AS PREDICTED, EVEN A DEEP-FRIED DISH!

734
00:28:33,945 --> 00:28:35,880
-It's not a fritter. It's <i>menbosha</i>.
-It's <i>menbosha</i>.

735
00:28:35,947 --> 00:28:38,249
So you are deep-frying something.

736
00:28:38,316 --> 00:28:39,784
<i>Menbosha </i>is a deep-fried dish.

737
00:28:39,851 --> 00:28:41,119
A perfect side dish for udon.

738
00:28:41,186 --> 00:28:42,787
It'll create a good balance.

739
00:28:42,854 --> 00:28:45,156
-A good balance.
-A good balance between the three dishes.

740
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:48,159
TEAM HYUN-SUK & POONG'S INGREDIENTS:
MIYEOK, BLUE CRAB

741
00:28:48,226 --> 00:28:50,161
VENUS CLAM, SHIITAKE,
CHICKEN STOCK, BREAD, LEMON

742
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:52,063
The name of our dish is

743
00:28:52,731 --> 00:28:54,399
BMB.

744
00:28:54,466 --> 00:28:56,634
We'll use blue crabs and <i>miyeok</i>

745
00:28:56,701 --> 00:29:00,672
and prepare a new kind of seaweed dish
you have never had before.

746
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:02,440
For the sauce,

747
00:29:02,507 --> 00:29:04,943
I wish to add lots of seaweed flavor, so…

748
00:29:05,009 --> 00:29:06,611
Actually, it's…

749
00:29:06,678 --> 00:29:07,512
HESITANT…

750
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:08,413
In America…

751
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:10,982
-He's going to grind it.
-Be quiet.

752
00:29:11,049 --> 00:29:12,584
-Will you grind it or not?
-Let's hear him.

753
00:29:12,650 --> 00:29:16,821
In American steak houses,
you'll find side dishes like crab cakes.

754
00:29:16,888 --> 00:29:18,556
-I want to add seaweed…
-Yes, we get it.

755
00:29:18,623 --> 00:29:20,225
Will you grind it or not?

756
00:29:20,291 --> 00:29:21,659
…to add flavor to the cake sauce.

757
00:29:21,726 --> 00:29:24,362
-To do that, will you grind it?
-Grind it?

758
00:29:25,563 --> 00:29:27,365
-He'll split it into molecules.
-That's right.

759
00:29:27,866 --> 00:29:30,502
SO HE'S GOING TO GRIND IT

760
00:29:30,802 --> 00:29:32,103
(FOR THE GUEST) IT'S A NEW METHOD!

761
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:33,338
Lastly, I thought we could

762
00:29:33,404 --> 00:29:37,041
-deep-fry the seaweed.
-Like <i>bugak?</i>

763
00:29:37,108 --> 00:29:39,210
Yes, it'll be something like <i>miyeok bugak</i>.

764
00:29:39,277 --> 00:29:41,312
K-Food <i>Miyeok </i>Hunters.

765
00:29:41,379 --> 00:29:44,983
Let us begin the 15-minute cook-off now.

766
00:29:45,049 --> 00:29:48,586
-I'm so excited.
-Once it begins, there's no going back.

767
00:29:48,653 --> 00:29:52,590
The team that's after
the Best Couple Award this year.

768
00:29:52,657 --> 00:29:56,094
Attention Hunters,
Jung Ho-young and Sam Kim.

769
00:29:56,161 --> 00:29:59,430
They're even willing to work
with their sworn enemy for a star.

770
00:29:59,497 --> 00:30:03,268
Star Hunters, Choi Hyun-suk and Kim Poong.

771
00:30:03,334 --> 00:30:07,906
Which team will hunt down
Director Kang's appetite?

772
00:30:07,972 --> 00:30:11,676
Let the 15-minute team round begin!

773
00:30:13,077 --> 00:30:14,445
The clock is ticking.

774
00:30:14,512 --> 00:30:15,713
Begin!

775
00:30:15,780 --> 00:30:17,015
THESE TWO SPLIT UP

776
00:30:17,081 --> 00:30:18,550
WHAT ABOUT THIS TEAM?

777
00:30:19,284 --> 00:30:20,118
A MINOR COLLISION

778
00:30:20,518 --> 00:30:21,553
IN HIS WAY

779
00:30:21,853 --> 00:30:22,687
SHAKY FROM THE START

780
00:30:22,754 --> 00:30:24,622
He's just standing around.

781
00:30:24,689 --> 00:30:25,690
STARING…

782
00:30:25,757 --> 00:30:26,658
What do I do?

783
00:30:26,724 --> 00:30:29,360
-Team Hyun-suk and Poong's first time.
-You told me to cut them!

784
00:30:29,427 --> 00:30:31,129
I'll cut them, so you can prep them later.

785
00:30:31,196 --> 00:30:32,664
-Poong stands around.
-You can wash them.

786
00:30:32,730 --> 00:30:35,033
Chef Hyun-suk can't give him a job.

787
00:30:35,099 --> 00:30:37,769
-He doesn't trust him.
-Hyun-suk preps the blue crabs.

788
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:40,305
-Don't talk back at me and do as I say.
-Fine.

789
00:30:40,371 --> 00:30:41,906
Don't say fine. Say, "Yes, Chef."

790
00:30:41,973 --> 00:30:42,907
Yes, Chef!

791
00:30:42,974 --> 00:30:45,076
"Do not talk back at me,"
and, "Yes, Chef!"

792
00:30:45,143 --> 00:30:46,211
Can you do this?

793
00:30:46,277 --> 00:30:48,613
-Yes, Chef!
-Poong gets simple jobs,

794
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:50,615
and Hyun-suk does the big jobs.

795
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:54,018
He cut the crabs already
and only let Poong clean them.

796
00:30:54,085 --> 00:30:55,453
We must remove the eggs.

797
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,322
-We're using just the meat.
-Just the meat?

798
00:30:57,388 --> 00:31:01,559
The eggs become harder when cooked,
so it can ruin the texture.

799
00:31:01,793 --> 00:31:02,627
BLUE CRAB, NO EGGS

800
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:04,829
Poong understands the dish too.

801
00:31:04,896 --> 00:31:05,797
-Of course.
-Throw it out to me.

802
00:31:06,097 --> 00:31:07,665
DERPY LAUGH
HAHAHAHAHA

803
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:09,734
THE HEAD CHEF GRABS HIS KNIFE!

804
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:12,036
2. FINELY CHOP AND STIR-FRY
ONION AND SHIITAKE

805
00:31:12,103 --> 00:31:15,139
Chef Hyun-suk begins to chop an onion.

806
00:31:15,206 --> 00:31:16,541
-Hey, Poong.
-Yes?

807
00:31:16,808 --> 00:31:17,942
I'LL GIVE YOU A JOB

808
00:31:18,009 --> 00:31:19,944
-Season the pan with salt.
-Salt?

809
00:31:20,011 --> 00:31:21,579
RUSHING OVER

810
00:31:21,646 --> 00:31:22,747
One, two, three.

811
00:31:24,682 --> 00:31:25,683
One, two, three.

812
00:31:28,119 --> 00:31:29,120
Performing in unison!

813
00:31:30,221 --> 00:31:32,357
Director Kang looks very happy.

814
00:31:32,423 --> 00:31:33,858
<i>-Double salt.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

815
00:31:33,925 --> 00:31:35,326
<i>This is what we call inspiration.</i>

816
00:31:35,393 --> 00:31:36,895
They even choreographed it.

817
00:31:37,262 --> 00:31:39,631
THE 6TH AND 7TH MEMBERS OF SAJA BOYS

818
00:31:40,098 --> 00:31:42,000
THE STAR HUNTERS
HAVE NO LOVE BUT ALL TEAMWORK

819
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:44,469
WHAT ABOUT THE ATTENTION HUNTERS?

820
00:31:44,535 --> 00:31:47,772
They've split up their tasks
in minute details.

821
00:31:47,839 --> 00:31:51,542
Sam is solely in charge
of making the <i>menbosha</i>.

822
00:31:51,809 --> 00:31:54,045
1. GRIND PORK BELLY, SHRIMP, EGG WHITE,
AND CHICKEN STOCK

823
00:31:54,112 --> 00:31:56,714
-Sam, are you making <i>menbosha?</i>
-That's right.

824
00:31:56,781 --> 00:31:58,549
-Sam's <i>menbosha</i>.
-Yes.

825
00:31:58,716 --> 00:32:00,118
WHAT'S HO-YOUNG STARTING WITH?

826
00:32:00,184 --> 00:32:01,452
Kelp and bonito flakes.

827
00:32:01,519 --> 00:32:04,455
He'll probably use those two
to make the broth.

828
00:32:04,689 --> 00:32:05,723
WHAT'S NEXT?

829
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:07,892
VEGGIES FOR THE SWEET AND SOUR
SEAWEED SALAD

830
00:32:07,959 --> 00:32:09,227
The sweet and sour salad.

831
00:32:09,294 --> 00:32:10,929
He's working on a cucumber.

832
00:32:11,796 --> 00:32:13,264
HIS SPECIALTY, FINE CUTS

833
00:32:13,331 --> 00:32:15,433
-His skills.
-It'll look like a spring.

834
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:17,535
-He's not cutting it off completely.
-It's like art.

835
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:18,469
It really is.

836
00:32:19,671 --> 00:32:21,439
He's an expert in Japanese cuisine.

837
00:32:21,506 --> 00:32:23,841
After making those cuts,

838
00:32:23,908 --> 00:32:26,577
he'll chop them into 5 cm pieces
and serve them with seaweed.

839
00:32:26,644 --> 00:32:28,146
-It's for good texture.
-Excellent texture.

840
00:32:28,212 --> 00:32:29,714
-It's for the salad?
-Yes.

841
00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:32,717
They've split their tasks
and are working on different things.

842
00:32:32,784 --> 00:32:34,218
-He's making <i>menbosha</i>.
-He is.

843
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:37,622
Sam is solely in charge
of making the <i>menbosha</i>.

844
00:32:37,689 --> 00:32:39,724
3. WRAP THE FILLING WITH SEAWEED

845
00:32:40,058 --> 00:32:41,726
NEXT, FRYING BATTER!

846
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:44,395
-Are you making frying batter?
-That's right.

847
00:32:45,196 --> 00:32:46,864
He'll deep-fry the seaweed.

848
00:32:46,931 --> 00:32:49,567
-I hope the thickness is right.
-I hope so.

849
00:32:50,134 --> 00:32:52,270
-This is a little thin.
-It's fine.

850
00:32:52,337 --> 00:32:54,605
Just add another coat of breadcrumbs.

851
00:32:54,906 --> 00:32:56,240
ADDING MORE BREADCRUMBS AS HE SAID

852
00:32:56,307 --> 00:32:57,709
They have good teamwork.

853
00:32:57,976 --> 00:33:00,044
HO-YOUNG BLANCHES ABALONE AND SHRIMP

854
00:33:00,111 --> 00:33:01,079
Two minutes have passed.

855
00:33:01,145 --> 00:33:02,347
Two minutes have passed.

856
00:33:02,413 --> 00:33:03,548
Time really flies.

857
00:33:03,614 --> 00:33:04,649
Right? It's already…

858
00:33:04,916 --> 00:33:06,150
WE HAVE NO TIME!

859
00:33:06,217 --> 00:33:09,187
-Onion.
-Onion. Did you stir-fry the onion?

860
00:33:09,253 --> 00:33:10,788
I'll beat the eggs.

861
00:33:10,855 --> 00:33:13,291
There's a hierarchy
between Hyun-suk and Poong.

862
00:33:13,358 --> 00:33:16,327
Poong moves
when Hyun-suk gives him an order.

863
00:33:16,594 --> 00:33:18,463
MAKING BREADCRUMBS!

864
00:33:18,529 --> 00:33:20,398
-I beat the eggs.
-Oh, okay.

865
00:33:20,465 --> 00:33:22,033
Poong grabs frying powder.

866
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:23,935
Will he deep-fry the seaweed?

867
00:33:24,002 --> 00:33:26,037
-I hope the thickness turns out right.
-I hope so.

868
00:33:26,104 --> 00:33:27,872
Right. Yes.

869
00:33:28,072 --> 00:33:28,906
SESAME OIL

870
00:33:28,973 --> 00:33:31,209
ALMOST FORGOT THE MAIN INGREDIENT,
SEAWEED

871
00:33:31,476 --> 00:33:34,779
3. STIR-FRY SEAWEED IN SESAME OIL

872
00:33:35,246 --> 00:33:36,948
CHICKEN STOCK

873
00:33:37,248 --> 00:33:38,149
AND RAMYEON SOUP BASE?

874
00:33:38,216 --> 00:33:39,550
<i>Ramyeon</i> soup base?

875
00:33:39,617 --> 00:33:43,021
-Is that <i>ramyeon</i> soup base?
-He mixed <i>ramyeon</i> soup and frying powder.

876
00:33:43,087 --> 00:33:44,922
You seemed to like <i>ramyeon.</i>

877
00:33:44,989 --> 00:33:46,924
-We were inspired by the awards ceremony
-Ceremony.

878
00:33:46,991 --> 00:33:48,559
-when you ate uncooked <i>ramyeon.</i>
<i>-Ramyeon</i>.

879
00:33:48,626 --> 00:33:50,595
Webtoon Artist Poong
is paying homage to you!

880
00:33:50,661 --> 00:33:51,763
-He's right!
-I see.

881
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:54,365
MAKING SURE THEY PROMOTE THEIR TEAM!

882
00:33:54,432 --> 00:33:56,401
This is what the Oscars are all about.

883
00:33:56,467 --> 00:33:58,469
You always need a story
for a film and a dish.

884
00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:01,205
Poong decided to use <i>ramyeon</i> soup base

885
00:34:01,272 --> 00:34:03,341
after seeing Maggie eat uncooked <i>ramyeon</i>
at the ceremony!

886
00:34:03,408 --> 00:34:07,011
-All creative works stem from inspiration.
-Precisely!

887
00:34:07,078 --> 00:34:08,413
-Sure, old man.
-Sure.

888
00:34:08,479 --> 00:34:10,314
-Old Man Choi.
-"Old Man Choi"?

889
00:34:10,381 --> 00:34:11,816
A word from Old Man Choi.

890
00:34:11,883 --> 00:34:13,017
He's old and wise.

891
00:34:13,251 --> 00:34:14,085
ANNOYED

892
00:34:14,152 --> 00:34:15,686
Old Man Choi,
who took a picture with a tank.

893
00:34:16,054 --> 00:34:17,021
THE OLD MAN'S ONCE UPON A TIME

894
00:34:17,088 --> 00:34:20,758
-He had his first banana in college.
-That's right.

895
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:22,660
HIS HISTORY IS AS LONG AS THE OSCARS

896
00:34:22,727 --> 00:34:24,695
-He even ate the skin.
-Right.

897
00:34:24,762 --> 00:34:27,632
He dried the skin and made tea.

898
00:34:27,698 --> 00:34:29,000
VENUS CLAM AND BLUE CRAB BROTH

899
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:32,003
4. POUR STRAINED BROTH
ON STIR-FRIED SEAWEED

900
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:33,337
Poong, salt this again.

901
00:34:33,404 --> 00:34:34,305
-Salt?
-Yes.

902
00:34:35,006 --> 00:34:36,174
One, two, three.

903
00:34:37,008 --> 00:34:37,842
One, two, three.

904
00:34:37,909 --> 00:34:39,177
SALT POP!

905
00:34:39,977 --> 00:34:40,912
Nothing went in.

906
00:34:42,647 --> 00:34:44,015
They have good teamwork.

907
00:34:44,081 --> 00:34:45,516
I can't believe I'm seeing this live.

908
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:47,618
Their teamwork isn't so bad.

909
00:34:47,685 --> 00:34:48,886
-Not bad.
-No.

910
00:34:48,953 --> 00:34:52,757
Sam and Ho-young aren't showing
the kind of performance they're showing.

911
00:34:52,824 --> 00:34:53,858
They work individually.

912
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:55,426
SHRIMP AND ABALONE, OUT

913
00:34:55,493 --> 00:34:57,095
SHRIMPS, INTO THE SWEET AND SOUR SALAD!

914
00:34:57,161 --> 00:34:59,163
Sam and Ho-young are way too quiet.

915
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:02,100
He's making zig zag cuts on the abalones.

916
00:35:02,166 --> 00:35:04,602
-He is?
-That way, he'll get more sauce on it.

917
00:35:06,037 --> 00:35:07,605
It looks so good.

918
00:35:08,539 --> 00:35:09,707
SOY SAUCE & VINEGAR

919
00:35:09,774 --> 00:35:10,641
6. MAKE SWEET AND SOUR SAUCE

920
00:35:10,708 --> 00:35:14,345
Sam just added lemon
and made sweet and sour soy sauce.

921
00:35:14,912 --> 00:35:16,714
-For the salad.
-That'll be a nice bite.

922
00:35:16,781 --> 00:35:18,082
You have 9 minutes and 30 seconds.

923
00:35:18,149 --> 00:35:20,051
He doesn't have much time,

924
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:22,053
but he's putting lots of work
into that udon.

925
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,121
Lots of work.

926
00:35:23,988 --> 00:35:25,123
I see.

927
00:35:25,189 --> 00:35:27,358
Ho-young is serious about making udon.

928
00:35:27,425 --> 00:35:28,392
7. MIX BROTH WITH CONDIMENTS

929
00:35:28,459 --> 00:35:30,094
What are you doing, Ho-young?

930
00:35:30,161 --> 00:35:32,196
I'm chilling the broth.

931
00:35:32,263 --> 00:35:35,032
Sam and Ho-young are moving fast
just as we expected.

932
00:35:35,366 --> 00:35:36,634
CHECKING THE TIME

933
00:35:36,701 --> 00:35:37,602
We're short on time.

934
00:35:38,035 --> 00:35:39,537
POONG PICKS OUT CRAB MEAT!

935
00:35:39,604 --> 00:35:40,838
It's still hot.

936
00:35:40,905 --> 00:35:42,039
I can do it.

937
00:35:42,507 --> 00:35:44,342
BOILED SEAWEED SOUP, OUT

938
00:35:44,408 --> 00:35:46,177
He'll split that into molecules.

939
00:35:46,244 --> 00:35:47,311
Correct.

940
00:35:47,378 --> 00:35:49,013
-Boo.
-He'll grind the <i>miyeok</i>.

941
00:35:49,347 --> 00:35:51,249
THE GUEST CHANGES, SO WHO CARES?

942
00:35:51,315 --> 00:35:52,383
A familiar scene, isn't it?

943
00:35:53,918 --> 00:35:56,454
It would be great
if someone held this for me!

944
00:35:56,521 --> 00:35:58,856
-Should I do it?
-Ignore him.

945
00:35:58,923 --> 00:36:00,791
He's putting him up for the job.

946
00:36:00,858 --> 00:36:02,560
-Hyun-suk tosses over the work.
-Crab meat.

947
00:36:02,927 --> 00:36:04,228
PUTS SOMEONE TO WORK AND HELPS POONG

948
00:36:04,295 --> 00:36:06,030
It's hot.

949
00:36:06,097 --> 00:36:08,099
-It's hot.
-I'll do it. I got three layers of gloves.

950
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:09,967
-It's okay. It's not hot. I got it.
-You got it?

951
00:36:10,234 --> 00:36:11,068
DOING THE TOUGH JOB

952
00:36:11,135 --> 00:36:13,004
This is why I put on
three layers of gloves.

953
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:13,938
DOESN'T EVEN FLINCH!

954
00:36:14,005 --> 00:36:15,873
Their teamwork doesn't seem so bad.

955
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,476
Chef Hyun-suk is making béchamel sauce.

956
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:20,878
It's not blending too well.

957
00:36:25,249 --> 00:36:27,752
SITS AWKWARDLY

958
00:36:28,386 --> 00:36:29,420
How long do I do this?

959
00:36:29,487 --> 00:36:30,421
Keep doing it.

960
00:36:31,522 --> 00:36:32,957
OH, WELL

961
00:36:33,024 --> 00:36:34,525
Why did you tell him to do that?

962
00:36:34,592 --> 00:36:37,495
-It's so loud. Come on.
-Come on.

963
00:36:38,296 --> 00:36:39,897
-Do you have to blend it?
-Sorry.

964
00:36:40,531 --> 00:36:42,800
Chef Ho-young kneads the dough.

965
00:36:42,867 --> 00:36:44,735
-He's making udon now.
-The noodles.

